Here is the follow up:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub3.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showMessage?topicID=1903.topic">pub3.ezboard.com/fbrellse...1903.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The point is that wizards using DD spells suck at damage over time.  They're great at short bursts of damage, but that is really only necessary in very limited situations (big raids mainly).  A wizard using AE spells is more efficient at damage over time, but this requires group coordination not necessary with another damage dealing class (say a Rogue, Monk, Warrior or pet class).<br>
<br>
It certainly doesn't show that enchanters are bad nukers.  The fact that we contribute any damage over the course of a dungeon crawl is significant, given everything else we contribute.  Wizards provide 2 things...  Evacs and Damage.  The post was meant to let people question how good they really are at one of those things.<br>
<br>
-Maryinn of the Merry Band (Brell Serilis)<br>
